<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-285-733  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 285 733.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Government Computer News  Jan 23 1989 v8 n2 p22(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Pub. Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Virex protects your Mac from those nasty bugs. (Software Review)(Apple Macintosh anti-viral measures) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Merrell, William J.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>HJC Software Inc's $99.95 Virex program detects three computerviruses that affect the Apple Macintosh.andP;  Virex diagnoses aprogram containing viral code, removes the virus, then restoresthe program to its normal condition.andP;  Virex detects and repairsthe Scores virus, the NVir family of viruses and the Peace virus.andO;The Scores virus is the most damaging and spreads quickly.andP;  TheNVir family adversely affects applications and the Peace virus isbelieved to be benign.andP;  Virex can check for the existence of otherviruses but cannot repair them, although a future updated versionof Virex will have that capability.andP;  Virex is a valuable programthat is easy to use and install and can be used with the Mac Plus,Mac SE and Mac II.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   HJC Software Inc. (products).andO;Product:   Virex (Data security software).andO;Topic:     Computer VirusesEvaluationSoftware Packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Virex Protects Your Mac From Those Nasty BugsandM;Recent alarm over computer viruses has prompted a growth industry inantiviral measures.andP;  While much attention has been given to networks andMS-DOS machines, relatively little has been done to protect the AppelMacintosh.andM;Now there is Virex from HJC Software Inc.andP;  Virex is designed to detect threeviruses known to plague Macintosh systems.andP;  It can diagnose an infectedprogram, remove the viral code and restore the program to its original state.andM;Virex comes on a single disk and is easy to install and operate.andP;  Simplyclicking the diagnose icon gives the option of scanning a hard disk, a floppydisk or a single file.andP;  If a virus is found, the file can be repaired withanother click.andM;Virex is limited to detecting and repairing three viruses known to HJC at thetime Virex was released:andM;* The Scores virus, which HJC says is probably the most damaging of the knownMacintosh viruses.andP;  Scores spreads rapidly by lying dormant before causingdamage.andM;* The NVir family of viruses.andP;  The virus is injected into applicationsoftware, which in turn infects the system folder.andP;  It causes applications tobehave erratically.andM;* The Peace virus.andP;  This bug displayed a message of peace on all infectedmachines on March 2, 1988, then self-destructed.andP;  Although supposedly benign,there still are occasional reports of file corruption.andM;Virex also checks for, but does not repair, viruses that are unknown to HJC.andO;HJC officials say Virex will be updated to detect and repair new viruses asthey become known.andM;Virex is compatible with Mac Plus, Mac SE and Mac II, using System 4.1, 5.0or 6.02.andP;  Virex comes with System 6.02 installed, so it can be used as a bootdisk.andM;Virex has two uses: examining the programs you have and the programs you aregoing to get.andP;  Once you know your system is uninfected, you can install Virexon your hard disk to screen new programs.andP;  It can be well worth the effort.andO;</TEXT></DOC>